  "texts": [
    "For instance, schemas describing synapses between two neurons contain two 'bound spatial points', which are associated with the pre-and postsynaptic segments but vary in their additional parameters (for example, size and neurotransmitter; Extended Data Fig. 5c).",
    "We identified the need for allowing users to add data entries to existing annotations without needing to copy the entire table.",
    "For this, we implemented reference schemas that define reference tables.",
    "A reference table is linked to another table via foreign key constraints (SQL) and may only contain data entries for a subset of the annotations in the referenced table (Extended Data Fig. 6).",
    "Compared to other tools 27, CAVE is designed to be flexible about how users define their annotations."
